    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Immigrants, Legal and Illegal</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Suffolk County Executive Steve Levy letter on March 11 editorial calling for rejection of his plan to control illegal immigrants and day laborers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your March 11 editorial ''Rejecting the Levy Way,'' regarding illegal immigration, is totally out of touch with mainstream America -- and Suffolk County. Those seeking to control our borders and enforce our housing codes and labor laws are called xenophobic.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your March 11 editorial ''Rejecting the Levy Way,'' regarding illegal immigration, is totally out of touch with mainstream America -- and Suffolk County. Those seeking to control our borders and enforce our housing codes and labor laws are called xenophobic.</p>
        <p>The Times once again has blurred the distinction between legal and illegal immigration. The hiring site you promote would use taxpayer dollars to facilitate the illegal hiring of workers by employers that refuse to pay taxes, insurance or workers' compensation.</p>
        <p>Would you also suggest that we have taxpayer-financed crack houses and prostitution dens so that we can get the crack addicts and prostitutes off the streets? Isn't the better idea to simply enforce the law?</p>
        <p>Steve Levy  Suffolk County Executive  Hauppauge</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
